    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Geth doesn't accept 0 gas priced txs. That's a security feature, otherwise you could spam the network indefinitely from accounts with no balance.\r\n\r\nThe only way to get around the gas price limits is to set certain accounts as `local`. That makes Geth ignore the price. Geth's miner will also prioritize local transactions over all else.\r\n\r\nThus, if you see a 0 price tx, that was explicitly made by the miner, or explicitly pre-approved by the miner. You can't do such a thing without miner collaboration (or mining your own block).",
